4 SYNOPSIS:
5 This bill would authorize certain county
6 commissions to establish regulations related to the
7 permitting, construction, placement, or operation of
8 solar farms.
9 This bill would also provide penalties for
10 violations and provide for an appeal process.
11
12
13 A BILL
14 TO BE ENTITLED
15 AN ACT
16
17 Relating to counties and municipalities; to authorize
18 certain county commission to establish regulations related to
19 the permitting, construction, placement, or operation of solar
20 farms; to provide penalties for violations; and to provide for
21 an appeal process.
22 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
23 Section 1. (a) For the purposes of this section, the
24 following terms have the following meanings:
25 (1) COUNTY COMMISSION. The governing body of any county
26 that borders the Gulf of Mexico.
27 (2) SOLAR FARM. A large-scale, ground-mounted
28 installation of photovoltaic panels, arrays, or reflectors
Page 1

installation of photovoltaic panels, arrays, or reflectors
SB358 INTRODUCED
29 designed to generate electricity for sale or use off-site.
30 (b)(1) In order to protect the coastline and watershed,
31 a county commission may adopt resolutions to regulate the
32 permitting, construction, placement, or operation of solar
33 farms in the county.
34 (2) A county commission may adopt resolutions
35 establishing standards, specifications, criteria, and
36 conditions relating to permitting, construction, placement, or
37 operation of solar farms in the unincorporated areas of the
38 county.
39 (3) A county commission may adopt resolutions to
40 establish and determine the appropriate locations where solar
41 farms may be located or allowed or to prohibit the same.
42 (c)(1) If any building or structure is erected,
43 constructed, altered, repaired, converted, operated, or
44 maintained, or if any land is used, in violation of this
45 section or any resolution adopted pursuant to this section,
46 the county commission, or any administrative officer
47 designated by the county commission, may institute any
48 appropriate action or proceeding to prevent, restrain,
49 correct, or abate the violation, prevent the use of any
50 building or structure, or to prevent any illegal act, conduct,
51 business, or misuse in or upon any premises regulated under
52 the authority conferred by this section.
53 (2) A county commission may adopt resolutions providing
54 for a penalty in the form of a fine of up to one thousand
55 dollars ($1,000) for any violation of this section or an
56 ordinance adopted pursuant to this section.
Page 2

ordinance adopted pursuant to this section.
SB358 INTRODUCED
57 (3) Any violation of this section or an ordinance
58 adopted pursuant to this section shall be a public nuisance.
59 (4) Upon a finding that a building or structure
60 violates the provisions of this section or any ordinance
61 adopted pursuant to this section, the county commission may
62 remove the building or structure, and all costs of the removal
63 shall be assessed against the landowner and recorded as a lien
64 on the property and may be enforced until satisfied.
65 (d) A county commission may levy permit and
66 applications fees to administer the resolutions adopted
67 pursuant to this section. The fees shall cover the cost of
68 administrative activities and the cost of reviewing
69 applications, including the costs or fees associated with any
70 experts or consultants necessary to assist the county in
71 reviewing applications.
72 (e) A county commission may adopt resolutions to
73 determine the terms or conditions of any exceptions or
74 exemptions from the provisions of this section or any
75 resolution adopted pursuant to this section. Any resolution
76 adopted pursuant to this section shall authorize a variance
77 process and a variance appeals process for any party aggrieved
78 by a final variance decision of the county commission to
79 appeal the decision to the circuit court.
80 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
81 1, 2026.
